---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog - Khasanbayev" description="My coding journey, creative thoughts, and real dev life stories">
  <Navigation />

  <main>
    <section class="blog-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-content fade-in">
          <h1>Khasanbayev's <span class="gradient-text">Dev Blog</span></h1>
          <p class="hero-subtitle">
            Real stories, code experiments, side project lessons, and thoughts from my desk.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="blog-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="blog-grid">

          <article class="blog-post featured fade-in-delay-1">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/63/6a/56/636a56f7c86d3924c9a5f22d58c55f4e.jpg" alt="Building a Telegram bot at midnight" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-badge">Featured</span>
                <span class="post-date">July 10, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Side Projects</span>
              </div>
              <h2>Building a Telegram Bot at Midnight</h2>
              <p>Coding until sunrise taught me more than just handling API calls: it’s about patience, unexpected bugs, and that extra coffee cup that keeps you going. From design ideas to deployment mishaps, every late-night session shapes better code and even better stories.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="blog-post fade-in-delay-2">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/07/13/91/0713915e6cce7c06be08288ea62371fe.jpg" alt="My daily dev setup" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-date">July 5, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Workflow</span>
              </div>
              <h3>My Simple Daily Coding Setup</h3>
              <p>Every morning starts with the same ritual: a fresh coffee, VSCode with my favorite extensions, and a playlist that keeps distractions away. These small, repeatable habits make it easier to dive into code, stay productive, and finish what I start.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="blog-post fade-in-delay-3">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/5d/c8/63/5dc8637e74fd17dea829ea06541c2b72.jpg" alt="Small wins" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-date">June 25, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Mindset</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Small Wins That Keep Me Motivated</h3>
              <p>One bug fixed, one new feature launched, or even refactoring messy code — small wins matter. They turn big goals into daily progress and remind me that growth in coding (and life) is always about consistent steps, not giant leaps.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="blog-post fade-in-delay-1">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/7b/db/81/7bdb8129330201e611b551075d858e9c.jpg" alt="Weekend coding" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-date">June 18, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Lifestyle</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Why I Code Even on Weekends</h3>
              <p>Coding on weekends isn’t just about work — it’s creative freedom. Side projects help me explore new tech, test crazy ideas, and keep the passion alive beyond deadlines and client tasks. It’s my way of keeping coding fun.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="blog-post fade-in-delay-2">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/93/83/59/938359e19ab1532ba2b52e8e3d4820e3.jpg" alt="Quick tips" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-date">June 10, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Tips & Tricks</span>
              </div>
              <h3>3 Quick Fixes I Use Every Day</h3>
              <p>From fast CSS resets that fix broken layouts, to tiny JS helpers that save minutes daily, and a couple of CLI shortcuts I rely on — these small fixes keep my workflow smooth and help me avoid daily frustrations.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="blog-post fade-in-delay-3">
            <div class="post-image">
              <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/cf/f5/e1/cff5e1cba8964bcaeaee87cf0eaecb59.jpg" alt="Why blogging" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="post-content">
              <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-date">June 1, 2025</span>
                <span class="post-category">Personal</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Why I Started Writing About Code</h3>
              <p>Writing isn’t just about sharing tutorials. For me, it’s a way to document my journey, capture lessons learned, and maybe help someone facing the same problems. It turns mistakes into guides and keeps me thinking deeply about what I build.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>



<style>
  .blog-hero {
    padding: 120px 0 80px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: #94A3B8;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .blog-content {
    padding: 0 0 80px;
  }

  .blog-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(380px, 1fr));
    gap: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .blog-post {
    background: rgba(51, 65, 85, 0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(71, 85, 105, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
  }

  .blog-post:hover {
    transform: translateY(-8px);
    border-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.5);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .blog-post.featured {
    grid-column: span 2;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    border-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.5);
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.05);
  }

  .post-image {
    height: 200px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .blog-post.featured .post-image {
    height: 100%;
  }

  .post-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .blog-post:hover .post-image img {
    transform: scale(1.05);
  }

  .post-content {
    padding: 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .post-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .post-badge {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3B82F6 0%, #8B5CF6 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  .post-date,
  .post-category {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #94A3B8;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .post-category {
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
    color: #60A5FA;
    padding: 4px 8px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .blog-post h2,
  .blog-post h3 {
    color: #E2E8F0;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .blog-post h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .blog-post h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .blog-post p {
    color: #94A3B8;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  .read-more {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    color: #3B82F6;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 14px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .read-more:hover {
    color: #60A5FA;
    transform: translateX(2px);
  }

  .pagination {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 32px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(71, 85, 105, 0.3);
  }

  .pagination-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 12px 20px;
    background: rgba(51, 65, 85, 0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(71, 85, 105, 0.3);
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #E2E8F0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .pagination-btn:hover:not(.disabled) {
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.5);
  }

  .pagination-btn.disabled {
    opacity: 0.5;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  .pagination-numbers {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .page-number {
    padding: 8px 12px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    color: #94A3B8;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .page-number.active {
    background: #3B82F6;
    color: white;
  }

  .page-number:hover:not(.active) {
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
    color: #60A5FA;
  }

  .page-dots {
    color: #64748B;
    padding: 0 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .blog-hero {
      padding: 100px 0 60px;
    }

    .blog-content {
      padding: 0 0 60px;
    }

    .blog-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 48px;
    }

    .blog-post.featured {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-column: span 1;
    }

    .pagination {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .pagination-numbers {
      order: -1;
    }
  }
</style>